### Version descent CFG

**Nodes** тАФ 11 version nodes arranged in three horizontal substrate bands:
- **Top band (Python, green):** `seed` (frob.py тАФ the meta-circular Frobenius check)
  and `v0.1` (ob3ect-imscriber.py тАФ Python Frobenius compiler, Closure: True)
- **Middle band (C/ELF, orange):** `v0.2` (custom .o grammar тЖТ C native binary),
  `v0.3` (quine embedding тАФ self.o imscribed in binary), `v0.4` (quine extraction stub),
  `v0.5` (QUINE opcode added), `v0.6` (MACRO opcode тАФ language deepening),
  `v0.7` (entropy pass тАФ ╬ФS тЙИ 0 verified), `v0.8` (full C self-hosting target),
  `v0.9` (pre-silicon тАФ final C generation)
- **Bottom band (Silicon/x86, gold):** `v0.10` тАФ bare-metal x86 bootloader ISO

**Edges** тАФ directed imscription edges (parent тЖТ child in the descent). Each edge
represents the IMASM morphism that compiles one generation into the next: the ob3ect
imscribing itself into a lower-substrate form.

**Cross-substrate leaps** тАФ two edges cross substrate boundaries: `v0.1 тЖТ v0.2`
(Python тЖТ C/ELF, the first substrate descent) and `v0.9 тЖТ v0.10` (C тЖТ Silicon,
the final bare-metal crossing). These are highlighted purple in Phase 1 and amber in
Phase 2 when the pulse is near them.

**Phase 1:** Versions appear in imscription order (seed тЖТ v0.1 тЖТ тАж тЖТ v0.10). When
`v0.10` first appears, it flashes gold and the title reads "тЖР bare metal!" тАФ the
completion of the descent from Python source to x86 bootloader.

**Phase 2:** Gaussian pulse travels the lineage from seed down to v0.10. The gold
Silicon node pulses brightest at the pulse peak. The title shows the current generation
and "10 generations ┬╖ ╬╝тИШ╬┤ = id" тАФ the descent composed with the return is identity.

![Descent CFG](digital/docs/cfg_descent.gif)

