## IMASM Instruction Set

The 12-opcode Imscribing Assembly. Every ob3ect maps all 12.

```
FAMILY      OPCODE   ROLE
тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФА
Logical     VINIT    Initial object тИЕ тАФ void / pre-imscription state
Logical     TANCH    Terminal anchor тКд тАФ closed, verified boundary
Logical     AFWD     Forward morphism тЖТ (construction / elaboration)
Logical     AREV     Contravariant тЖР (descent / deconstruction)
Logical     CLINK    Composition тИШ (sequential chaining)
Logical     IMSCRIB   Identity id тАФ self-reference, the ob3ect reading itself

Frobenius   FSPLIT   Comultiplication ╬┤: A тЖТ AтКЧA (branching / parsing)
Frobenius   FFUSE    Multiplication ╬╝: AтКЧA тЖТ A  (reconstitution / unparsing)
             тЖ│ FFUSE must satisfy ╬╝тИШ╬┤ = id тАФ this is the Frobenius gate
             тЖ│ FFUSE has TWO modes:
               CANONICAL:  FFUSE(BOTH) тЖТ TRUE  (standard identity)
               DIALETHEIC: FFUSE(BOTH) тЖТ BOTH  (paradox identity)
               Dialetheic mode is auto-detected from EVALT/EVALF context.

Dialetheia  EVALT    True lattice тАФ affirmative branch
Dialetheia  EVALF    False lattice тАФ negative / error branch
Dialetheia  ENGAGR   Both тАФ paradox held without resolution (Priest dialetheism)

Linear      IFIX     ROM fixation тАФ permanent, irreversible commitment
```

**The canonical bootstrap sequence** across all IMASM systems:

```
IMSCRIB тЖТ AREV тЖТ FSPLIT тЖТ AFWD тЖТ FFUSE тЖТ CLINK тЖТ IFIX тЖТ IMSCRIB
```

This is ╬╝тИШ╬┤ = id as an eight-step categorical assembly. The loop closes on
IMSCRIB тАФ the final step is self-reference, making the loop autopoietic.

**Dialetheic variant** (identity is BOTH, not TRUE):

```
IMSCRIB тЖТ EVALT тЖТ FSPLIT тЖТ EVALF тЖТ FFUSE тЖТ ENGAGR тЖТ IFIX тЖТ IMSCRIB
```

Only the EVALT/EVALF order matters тАФ whichever fires first sets the context
that FFUSE reads. If both T and F are designated in the split interval,
dialetheic mode activates and the vessel holds paradox.

### Autopoietic Bootstrap Mechanics

The displayed 8-step sequences are **compressed linear paths** through the bootstrap's execution graph. The graph contains branch points at CLINK that the linear form collapses.

**Compressed** (what the sequence notation encodes):

```
VINITтЖТIMSCRIBтЖТAREVтЖТFSPLIT
         тЦ▓             тФВ
         тФВ             тЦ╝
         тФВ            AFWD
         тФВ             тФВ
         тФВ             тЦ╝
        IFIXтЧДтФАтФАCLINKтЧДтФАFFUSE
```

**Decompressed** (the full structural picture):

```
VINITтЖТIMSCRIBтЖТAREVтЖТFSPLIT
        тЦ▓   тЦ▓           тФВ
        *   тФФтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФР     тЦ╝
     ****         тФВ    AFWD
     *            тФВ     тФВ
     тЦ╝            тФВ     тЦ╝
    IFIX........CLINKтЧДтФАFFUSE
```

`*` = back-prop & LinFix &nbsp; `.` = empty edge &nbsp; `тФВ` = weighted edge

Three distinct edges operate at the CLINKтАУIMSCRIBтАУIFIX triad:

**Empty edge (CLINK тЖТ IFIX):** CLINK emits a null composition directly to IFIX along the dotted path. This records the compositional event as an irreversible ROM fixation тАФ the witness that composition occurred тАФ regardless of whether the resulting morphism carries new structural content.

**Weighted edge (CLINK тЖТ IMSCRIB):** CLINK forwards the actual composed morphism up the `тФФтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФР` path to IMSCRIB. IMSCRIB receives it, self-imscribes, and re-enters the loop at AREV. This is the edge that makes the bootstrap autopoietic: the loop consumes its own composition as input to the next winding.

**Back-propagation: IMSCRIB тЖТ IFIX (LinFix):** After self-imscription, IMSCRIB emits a back-propagation (`****`) to IFIX, burning a second permanent record тАФ the completed loop iteration itself тАФ into ROM before the next winding begins.

The compressed sequence `... тЖТ CLINK тЖТ IFIX тЖТ IMSCRIB` shows one path through this structure. IFIX at position 6 is the collapsed arrival point of both the empty edge (from CLINK) and the back-prop (from IMSCRIB); IMSCRIB at position 7 represents the loop closure. The weighted CLINK тЖТ IMSCRIB edge and the back-prop IMSCRIB тЖТ IFIX edge are real structural edges that the 8-token notation does not make explicit.

**Dialetheic variant:** the dialetheic bootstrap places ENGAGR in the CLINK role. The branching structure is identical тАФ ENGAGR sends the empty edge to IFIX and the weighted edge to IMSCRIB; IMSCRIB back-props to IFIX тАФ but the register content on the weighted edge is Bтмб (BOTH, paradox held without collapse) rather than T (TRUE). IFIX therefore records Bтмб in the dialetheic case, which is why Class I terminates at Bтмб rather than T.

Every bootstrap winding generates exactly two IFIX records: one from CLINK's empty edge (compositional witness) and one from IMSCRIB's back-prop (self-reference witness). The loop is not merely self-referential тАФ it is self-recording. Each iteration imscribes both *what it composed* and *that it existed*.

