## Lean 4 Proofs

`proofs/` contains machine-checked Lean 4 formalizations of the tower's coherence laws,
with 13 `.lean` files plus a `lakefile.toml` and `lean-toolchain` for Mathlib v4.28.0.

```
proofs/
тФЬтФАтФА Frobenius.lean         тАФ Special Frobenius condition ╬╝тИШ╬┤ = id
тФЬтФАтФА Hopf.lean              тАФ Antipode involution SтИШS = id
тФЬтФАтФА Monad.lean             тАФ Monad laws (left unit, right unit, associativity)
тФЬтФАтФА CCC.lean               тАФ Cartesian closed category structure
тФЬтФАтФА Topos.lean             тАФ Topos axioms (subobject classifier, power objects)
тФЬтФАтФА Quantum.lean           тАФ Quantum measurement as Frobenius collapse
тФЬтФАтФА LinearLogic.lean       тАФ Linear logic resource accounting
тФЬтФАтФА HoTT.lean              тАФ Univalence for semantic equivalence classes
тФЬтФАтФА StringDiagrams.lean    тАФ Graphical calculus (snake, spider, monad wire)
тФЬтФАтФА SelfImscription.lean   тАФ Self-imscription coordinate stability proof
тФЬтФАтФА Coherence.lean         тАФ Cross-layer coherence conditions
тФЬтФАтФА TowerCoherence.lean    тАФ Tower coherence summary
тФФтФАтФА GrandCoherence.lean     тАФ Grand coherence across all layers

тФЬтФАтФА lakefile.toml          тАФ Lake build configuration (Mathlib v4.28.0)
тФЬтФАтФА lean-toolchain         тАФ Lean version pinning
```

These proofs correspond to the `proofbridge` layer in the digital tower. The ProofBridge
ob3ect holds a live pointer to this directory and verifies that the Lean build passes.
Build with:

```bash
cd proofs && lake build
```

Or use the provided script:

```bash
bash scripts/check_proofs.sh
```

